  "articleSummary": "The article argues that public LLM benchmarks are largely irrelevant for most businesses, which should instead prioritize custom, task-specific evaluation suites to accurately measure real-world performance and prevent quality regressions. It critiques reliance on \"vibes-based\" monitoring and generic LLM-as-judge approaches, advocating for a pragmatic evaluation spectrum that emphasizes deterministic checks, explicit failure definitions, and continuous CI/CD regression testing. Using the \"golden set\" framing—where production failures are systematically converted into automated test cases—the piece provides a practical, code-backed guide for engineering teams. The tone is sharply pragmatic and slightly satirical toward industry hype, targeting AI engineers, ML practitioners, and technical product leaders building production LLM systems.",
